cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use or reference this work, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
title: "Eight Sessions or Eight Years? A Structured Narrative Review of Therapy Duration for Complex Developmental Trauma"
abstract: >-
  Structured narrative review using critical interpretive synthesis (CIS) methodology,
  drawing on 89 sources across six epistemological layers — academic literature,
  naturalistic outcome studies, counterpoint evidence, practitioner essays, client
  narratives, and memoirs. Proposes a 4-factor framework (safety prerequisite,
  endpoint level, structural depth, elapsed time) that resolves the field's apparent
  disagreement about therapy duration by showing it is an artefact of unstated
  endpoint definitions. This review was conducted with substantial AI assistance
  (Claude Opus 4.6, Anthropic); see 2_methods/13_ai_methodology.md for the full
  division of labor.
authors:
